OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FOne of Britain's oldest surviving
OL,8,Fannual traditions has returned to the
OL,9,FRiver Thames as Swan Upping made its
OL,10,Fjourney along the river to Shepperton.
OL,12,FDating back hundreds of years, Swan
OL,13,FUpping is a five-day census of mute
OL,14,Fswans.
OL,16,FThe eye-catching tradition is carried
OL,17,Fout every July by the King's Swan
OL,18,FMarker and teams of skilled rowers,
OL,19,Fknown as Swan Uppers, who travel the
OL,20,Friver in traditional wooden skiffs.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FTheir job is to count the swans, check
OL,8,Ftheir health and record the number of
OL,9,Fcygnets born this year.
OL,11,FAny birds needing treatment are
OL,12,Fcarefully examined by vets before
OL,13,Fbeing released back onto the river.
OL,15,FDavid Barber, swan marker to his
OL,16,FMajesty the King explains: "The swan
OL,17,Fin early days, like swan upping, it
OL,18,Fwas all about a very important food
OL,19,Fand swan upping on the River Thames
OL,20,Fhas taken place since the 12th Century.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,F"And the swan was an important food
OL,8,Fand it was served up at banquets and
OL,9,Ffeasts.
OL,11,F"Of course, today the swan is no
OL,12,Flonger eaten, and it is a protected
OL,13,Fspecies. So swan upping is all about
OL,14,Fconservation and education."
OL,16,FDuring the 1980s the number of
OL,17,Fbreeding swan pairs collapsed to
OL,18,Fdangerously low levels, due to
OL,19,Fpoisoning from anglers' lead weights.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FA lead ban has helped restore swan
OL,8,Fnumbers, but they are still far lower
OL,9,Fthan pre-World War II levels.
OL,11,FMuch of the UK and Europe is enduring
OL,12,Fanother heat wave in what is proving
OL,13,Fto be one of the hottest years on
OL,14,Frecord.
OL,16,FThe heat is causing wildfires and
OL,17,Fdevastation in many places but
OL,18,Faccording to David Barber the swans
OL,19,Fare unphased by hot weather.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,F"Now we have the hot weather it's not
OL,8,Fso bad for swans, but naturally for
OL,9,Fother birds, wild birds, sparrows,
OL,10,Fwoodpeckers, that type of thing,
OL,11,Fthey're suffering," Mr Barber said.
OL,13,F"But the swans, they try and find
OL,14,Flet's say bushes or little creeks to
OL,15,Fgo up. So they get a little bit of
OL,16,Fshade and so they don't get so hot,"
OL,17,Fhe explained.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FBut for the humans taking part in swan
OL,8,Fupping the heat can be more
OL,9,Fproblematic. Everybody is hydrating
OL,10,Fwith lots of water, especially those
OL,11,Fbehind the oars.
OL,13,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,14,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,15,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,16,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,18,FJerry McCarthy is swan barge master
OL,19,Ffor Dyer's and has been taking part in
OL,20,Fswan upping for over 30 years.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FHe said: "Well it's nice because
OL,8,Fthere's a breeze, actually, on the
OL,9,Friver. But in the locks it can get
OL,10,Fquite hot, because obviously the heat
OL,11,Fis.
OL,13,F"But once we get out on the river it's
OL,14,Ffine, because we've got a nice breeze
OL,15,Fto cool us down."
OL,17,FLuckily for those rowing the skiffs
OL,18,Fthere are tow boats along the route
OL,19,Falways on hand ready to throw a rope
OL,20,Fto any oarsmen that need a break.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FThe British monarch traditionally
OL,8,Fclaims ownership of all unmarked Mute
OL,9,FSwans in open water.
OL,11,FWhen the swan uppers spot a group of
OL,12,Fthe birds they alert one another with
OL,13,Fthe cry of "All Up".
OL,15,FThe swans are corralled by the boats,
OL,16,Fknown as skiffs, and plucked from the
OL,17,Fwater - if they can be caught!
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1784117904
OL,3,CSwan Upping returns to the Thames as
OL,4,Ccenturies-old tradition visits
OL,5,CShepperton
OL,7,FThe event always attracts visitors to
OL,8,Fthe area to send the skiffs on their
OL,9,Fway, local MP Lincoln Jopp says swan
OL,10,Fupping is an important fixture in the
OL,11,Flocal calendar.
OL,13,FHe said: "It's a proper health check
OL,14,Fon the state of the river. Because the
OL,15,Fnumber of cygnets is monitored every
OL,16,Fyear. And, it's also a wonderful
OL,17,Fspectacle and a thoroughly important
OL,18,Fpart of the English summer."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
